- 'gardeners' refer to active users in the system;
- 'gardens' refer to portfolios managed by these users;
- 'wealth of their flora' refers to the total value of the portfolios.

'John Doe' refers to the user in question; 'Apple Inc.' is the asset or stock in focus; 'Retirement' portfolio refers to the 'golden years savings account'.;
The phrase 'golden years' is often used metaphorically to refer to the retirement period.;
The term 'holding' in finance generally means owning a stock or other asset.;

- 'particular stock' refers to stock_id = 102;
- 'specific data source' refers to source_id = 0;
- 'particular compliance check' refers to compliance_id = 1;
- Exchange ID 0 refers to a specific stock market exchange;
- Performance includes the opening, highest, lowest, and closing prices of the stock.
